Description: Body sherd of East Greek, possibly South Ionian, pottery closed vessel; exterior reserved save for single painted dot rosette; inscription on exterior. Fine micaceous light buff clay.
Curator's comments: Orientation of sherd uncertain; if the inscription is orthograde (and not cut upside-down), it is from the lower wall.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GE.931)
